1
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:13,067
We haven't heard
anything about...

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,333
our friend.

3
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:17,033
Yes, perhaps you know
something we don't.

4
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,667
Are you implying that
I'm not worried about my mom?

5
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,767
That I don't care about her?
Is that it?

6
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,667
- No, Auntie.
- Is that what you think of me?

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,167
You want to conspire with me
against Emma and Danilo?

8
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:29,333
I saw my husband go inside
with his mistress!

9
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:31,533
Mistresses should be whipped.

10
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:32,833
Nailed to the cross.

11
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:34,367
Buried alive.

12
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,967
Burned in hell.

13
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:36,867
- Danilo!
- Dan!

14
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,567
- Dan!
- Danilo!

15
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,067
You drove me crazy?

16
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:42,767
You're a monster!

17
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:48,000
I can't handle this.
Your dad got in an accident!

18
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:50,367
Mookie and I are so happy
in our own little bubble.

19
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,467
Then you came along
and ruined it!

20
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,633
Did I hear it right?

21
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:55,900
Olive?

22
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:36,533
Well, I wish I had
Olive's courage.

23
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:38,867
So I can stop you
from pestering us!

24
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,200
And what are you talking about?

25
00:01:42,367 --> 00:01:45,433
Didn't you abandon
Danilo and Mookie?

26
00:01:45,567 --> 00:01:51,100
So I ended up taking care
of them instead of you.

27
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:54,533
And now you have the guts
to show yourself here?

28
00:01:56,567 --> 00:01:57,867
Technically...

29
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,700
I didn't take them away
from you, Emma.

30
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,833
You abandoned them.

31
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:05,533
I will never abandon them!

32
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,200
And I wouldn't be out
of the picture

33
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:10,000
if you didn't ruin my life!

34
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:14,033
You were behind all the bad
things that happened to me.

35
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,367
And you know
what I'm talking about.

36
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,633
Proof...

37
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:18,800
or it didn't happen.

38
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:23,767
Ma'am Emma, the patient
is asking for you.

39
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:32,200
Dan.

40
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:42,567
I still haven't heard from them.

41
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:45,500
Should I go to the hospital?

42
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:47,433
Mookie, calm down.

43
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:51,800
I'm sure your mom and Aunt Jade
are taking care of him.

44
00:02:51,933 --> 00:02:53,833
He's right, Mookie. And...

45
00:02:53,967 --> 00:02:55,700
there might be trouble
brewing there!

46
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:57,667
That's right, I agree.

47
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,533
Since the rivals
are in one place.

48
00:02:59,667 --> 00:03:01,733
The more reason
I need to go there.

49
00:03:01,867 --> 00:03:05,633
Because they might start
fighting.

50
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:07,733
I have to go.

51
00:03:11,033 --> 00:03:12,333
Mookie!

52
00:03:12,467 --> 00:03:13,400
Dan.

53
00:03:13,533 --> 00:03:15,500
Dan, forgive me.

54
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:18,067
You got hurt because of me.

55
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:21,733
If only I'd been careful,
I could have stopped Jade.

56
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:24,300
This wouldn't have happened
to you.

57
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:27,500
I'm so worried. I thought
I was going to lose you.

58
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:29,400
Emma...

59
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:31,300
don't worry.

60
00:03:31,433 --> 00:03:32,633
I'm okay.

61
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:35,867
You didn't have to save me.

62
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,567
I can take care of myself.

63
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:41,800
Emma, do you remember
when we got together?

64
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,733
I made a promise to you...

65
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:45,967
and your mom.

66
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,767
That I will take care of you.
I will protect you.

67
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,200
Emma, I'm the one
who made a mistake.

68
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:55,733
I broke all my promises.

69
00:03:57,533 --> 00:04:00,433
So please, let me do this, Emma.

70
00:04:00,567 --> 00:04:04,000
Let me love you
as I promised you before.

71
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,567
<i> I will kill you, Emma.</i>

72
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:13,000
<i>If you don't put a stop to this.</i>

73
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:18,567
Hi, Miss. Do you have a patient
named Danilo Joseco here?

74
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,700
Ma'am, he's in cubicle two.

75
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:23,200
Baby girl.

76
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,367
Baby girl.

77
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,433
Dad!

78
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,900
Mookie.

79
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:33,733
Let them have a moment together
as a family.

80
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:36,000
Are you her mom?

81
00:04:36,133 --> 00:04:38,400
Yes, don't meddle, please.

82
00:04:38,533 --> 00:04:39,500
Okay?

83
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:43,400
Dad, how are you?

84
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,767
Are you okay?
Is your head still hurting?

85
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:47,567
Do you feel nauseous?
Are you dizzy?

86
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,800
- Do you need anything?
- Calm down, Dear.

87
00:04:49,933 --> 00:04:51,300
I'm okay.

88
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:56,733
Emma!

89
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:58,167
How are you?

90
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,267
I'm just going to get some air.

91
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:05,000
Mookie's a bit rattled.
She's worried about her dad.

92
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:07,867
I'm going to let
them be for now.

93
00:05:15,367 --> 00:05:16,733
Hey!

94
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:18,167
Jade!

95
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,200
I'm going to follow them.

96
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:21,000
Aunt Jade might do something
to Aunt Emma.

97
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:23,467
It's okay,
we'll take care of them.

98
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,567
You should go home.

99
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:27,667
- Your mom might get mad at us.
- He's right.

100
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,900
- Let's go, Kutsy.
- Okay, let's go.

101
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:37,533
Thank you for your concern,
Mookie.

102
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:41,167
The doctor advised me
to get some rest.

103
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,900
And I will be released soon.

104
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:44,667
Dad...

105
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,100
you scared me.

106
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:49,600
I thought I was going
to lose you, too.

107
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,667
I thought you were going
to leave me, too.

108
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:56,933
Dad...

109
00:05:57,067 --> 00:05:59,367
we still have a lot to fix.

110
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,800
We still have to talk to mom,
right?

111
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:08,100
Where did mom go?

112
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,933
I thought we were going
to talk things out.

113
00:06:54,367 --> 00:06:56,733
Let me guess why
you're sulking right now.

114
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:00,367
First, because...

115
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:03,067
Mookie ignored you.

116
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:06,567
Or maybe because...

117
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:09,467
she told you to leave
Danilo alone.

118
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,867
Which is which?

119
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:15,600
You really won't leave me alone?

120
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:17,533
You know what, Emma?

121
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:20,233
None of us will have peace

122
00:07:20,367 --> 00:07:25,667
if we both want to be
in Danilo and Mookie's lives.

123
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,233
Look at us now.

124
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:31,300
One of us should have left
this hospital.

125
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:33,300
If there's anyone that
doesn't belong here...

126
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:35,567
that's you.

127
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:39,067
My husband asked for me earlier.

128
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,233
You're stupid not being able
to understand that.

129
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:45,200
I'm not stupid.

130
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:46,933
I just don't back down easily.

131
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,433
I won't give up...

132
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:50,800
without a fight.

133
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:54,067
You know what?

134
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:56,367
That's actually a good idea.

135
00:07:56,500 --> 00:08:01,967
Since you're into cheap
altercations and confrontations.

136
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,533
Why don't we just fight
over Danilo?

137
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,800
Whoever wins...

138
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,767
gets him.

139
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:14,133
I don't know where you get
the nerve to talk like that.

140
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:17,267
Let's do a one-on-one fight.

141
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,433
Hand to hand.

142
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,600
Whoever wins
between the two of us...

143
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:26,533
gets Danilo.

144
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:28,733
Game?

145
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:32,133
You're the only one
who likes trouble.

146
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,533
You're the reason
we're here in the first place.

147
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:36,400
You ruined my family.

148
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,200
If you're looking
for a fight,

149
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:42,200
go over there!
Find someone to spar with!

150
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:44,900
We haven't even started yet.

151
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:47,167
And you're backing down already.

152
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,000
So...

153
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:50,467
you won't even...

154
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,267
put up a fight?

155
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,233
So, I'll be a winner by default?

156
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,033
I thought...

157
00:08:56,167 --> 00:08:58,633
you'd do anything for Danilo.

158
00:08:58,767 --> 00:08:59,933
So...

159
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:02,233
you're all talk?

160
00:09:02,367 --> 00:09:04,667
You didn't mean it when
you said you love him

161
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,500
and will do anything for him.
Is that it?

162
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,500
I will do anything
for my family.

163
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,367
For Danilo and Mookie.

164
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:17,100
So if I am
to take your challenge,

165
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:20,067
perhaps we should make
the prize bigger.

166
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,033
You won't just get Danilo.

167
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:23,700
You will also get Mookie.

168
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:25,967
And if you lose,

169
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:28,633
you will leave my family alone.

170
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,167
Winner takes all.

171
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:38,300
Nothing to say now?

172
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,033
I guess, you're all talk.

173
00:09:44,367 --> 00:09:45,433
Game.

174
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:48,333
Whoever wins...

175
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,600
gets Danilo and Mookie.

176
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,800
So if I win,

177
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:58,567
you will never
see them ever again.

178
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:01,667
Deal. Where to?

179
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,433
Calm down.

180
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:05,533
I challenged you,

181
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,600
so I will pick the place.

182
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:10,067
See you.

183
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,200
Boss, that's enough.

184
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:37,567
One only? I asked for two.

185
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,633
Give me more!

186
00:10:39,767 --> 00:10:42,100
Boss, that's enough.
You'll get a hangover.

187
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:43,833
One more!

188
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:45,667
Leave me alone.

189
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,833
I want to drink more.

190
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,567
You already drank a lot, Boss.

191
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,600
I'm okay. I can drink some more.

192
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,500
Come and drink with me.

193
00:11:00,467 --> 00:11:02,600
You'll be fine, Sir.
It's just a woman.

194
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:04,667
Rendall!

195
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:10,367
Really? Rendall?

196
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:11,967
Why?

197
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:15,533
Am I embarrassing myself?
Do you want me to stop drinking?

198
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:17,167
Am I making a mess?

199
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,500
Will I make my mom angry?

200
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:20,967
Am I making a fool of myself?

201
00:11:22,033 --> 00:11:24,867
Boss, there's a lot
of women out there.

202
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,833
If I were you,

203
00:11:25,967 --> 00:11:28,033
I'd let Ma'am Emma go.

204
00:11:36,867 --> 00:11:40,200
You have a lot of courage.

205
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,233
Can you say that again?

206
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,067
Boss.

207
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,133
Say that again.

208
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:44,667
- It's nothing, Sir.
- Say it again.

209
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:45,567
It's nothing.

210
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,033
Boss, that's enough.

211
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:51,167
Take back what you said.

212
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,367
Sorry, Boss.

213
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:53,733
I didn't mean it.

214
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,567
Don't let Ma'am Emma go.

215
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,367
- I will never let her go.
- Boss!

216
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,900
- Boss!
- Boss!

217
00:12:01,033 --> 00:12:04,633
I will do everything...

218
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:08,433
to make her come back to me.

219
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:10,567
Is that clear?

220
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:12,000
Yes, Sir.

221
00:12:19,433 --> 00:12:21,267
Hold this.

222
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:09,333
Why did you have to pick
this place?

223
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:10,567
We could have fought
on the street,

224
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:12,367
so we can go straight
to your funeral.

225
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:17,500
I picked this place
because it's quiet here.

226
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:19,000
It's private.

227
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:20,467
And it's just the two of us.

228
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,600
So you won't get to escape.

229
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:26,367
What?

230
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,167
Are you scared?

231
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:30,567
You can still back out.

232
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:33,467
But if you do,

233
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:37,133
you will never get to see
Danilo and Mookie again.

234
00:13:37,267 --> 00:13:38,800
Forever.

235
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:41,467
I know how you play
your game, Jade.

236
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,367
So don't worry...

237
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,867
because I will fight
for my family.

238
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,033
To live peacefully
once I get rid of you!

239
00:13:49,167 --> 00:13:51,567
Keep dreaming.

240
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,333
This seems easy enough.

241
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,233
Let me go!

242
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:08,733
You will feel real pain
once you lose Danilo and Mookie.

243
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,433
If you can't escape
once I count to three,

244
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:12,633
then this is over!

245
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:14,367
You have to leave
my family alone!

246
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,567
One!

247
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:18,367
I will never give up!

248
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,867
I'm not a quitter!

249
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,400
I'm not going to give up!

250
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:22,567
Two!

251
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:26,700
I'm the great one!

252
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:28,433
I'm the strong one!

253
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,767
And I'm the smart one!

254
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,333
Three!

255
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,300
What now?

256
00:14:45,433 --> 00:14:46,433
What?

257
00:14:46,567 --> 00:14:48,433
I always win!

258
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:49,700
Always!

259
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:53,133
This fight will not be over
if I'm not the winner!

260
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,367
A challenge?

261
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,400
Why didn't you tell me
about this sooner?

262
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:01,000
I'm sorry, Mookie.

263
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:04,567
We're supposed to keep
it a secret.

264
00:15:04,733 --> 00:15:06,967
But we're getting anxious.

265
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:09,633
This is driving us crazy.

266
00:15:09,767 --> 00:15:13,400
You shouldn't have let
them fight.

267
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:15,467
As if they'll listen to us.

268
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,333
Right.

269
00:15:17,467 --> 00:15:19,833
Okay, just come with me.

270
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:21,133
Mookie, wait!

271
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:23,067
Mookie, your mom
will get mad at us!

272
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,800
Hey!

273
00:15:24,933 --> 00:15:25,833
Right on cue.

274
00:15:26,767 --> 00:15:28,667
So now, Emma,

275
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:32,733
there's nothing left to do
but to get rid of you!

276
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:36,600
You want to take Danilo
and Mookie away from me?

277
00:15:36,767 --> 00:15:39,967
You won't get to see them again.

278
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:42,533
Over my dead body.

279
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:44,400
Or better yet...

280
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:45,733
over yours!

281
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:49,000
Because I will get to bury you!

282
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:52,933
I will bury you
before you get the chance!

283
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:04,900
You will never win against me,
Emma!

284
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:11,333
You monster!

285
00:16:11,467 --> 00:16:14,333
You're taking everything
from me!

286
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,100
You're a brute!

287
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:20,700
You've always been a pain
in my ass!

288
00:16:20,833 --> 00:16:23,933
You do nothing
but cause me trouble!

289
00:16:24,067 --> 00:16:25,100
Give me that!

290
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:31,533
I will end your life
once and for all!

291
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:33,267
<i> Remember,</i>

292
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,500
<i>a war is also a battle of wits.</i>

293
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:37,000
<i> And you have to be quick.</i>

294
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:41,100
<i>You need the determination
to win.</i>

295
00:17:00,067 --> 00:17:01,033
Emma...

296
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,933
what are you doing?

297
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:08,267
How can I help you, Ligaya?

298
00:17:09,467 --> 00:17:10,400
Martinez!

299
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:11,500
Martinez!

300
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,433
Hey, Ador.

301
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,467
Martinez...

302
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:17,567
I'm glad to see you.

303
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:19,767
I've been looking
for you for days now.

304
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,967
I just couldn't get to you.

305
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,033
I have nothing to give you yet.

306
00:17:24,167 --> 00:17:26,100
That's not the reason
why I'm here.

307
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:28,000
Please help me.

308
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:31,467
Please help me save my wife.

309
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,800
The one you
were telling me about?

310
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:36,833
Where is she now?

311
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:38,300
What happened to her?

312
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:42,000
She's locked up
in Olive's mansion.

313
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:44,700
I mean Jade Caparas.

314
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,233
Oh my, Ador.

315
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:50,900
Are you messing with me?

316
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:52,400
I'm not fooling around.

317
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:55,567
We might run out of time.

318
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,367
Something bad
might happen to Ligaya.

319
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:01,167
But Ador,

320
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,667
we can't just barge in there.

321
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:06,667
Especially if we don't
have a search warrant.

322
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:11,300
And she doesn't
even have a record.

323
00:18:11,433 --> 00:18:12,867
Can't you do it?

324
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:18,233
Not as a police officer,

325
00:18:18,367 --> 00:18:20,133
but as a friend.

326
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:26,067
I've had a lot of shortcomings
with my wife,

327
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,233
now's the right time for me
to make it up to her.

328
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:38,933
Emma, please!

329
00:18:39,067 --> 00:18:39,767
What now?

330
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:43,133
Why are you so scared?

331
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:45,200
You were full of courage
earlier!

332
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:47,433
Cause you have someone with you?

333
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:50,433
You know that you'll lose
if it's a fair fight!

334
00:18:50,567 --> 00:18:52,267
That's why you cheated!

335
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,300
But no matter what you do,

336
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:56,900
I will never give you
what doesn't belong to you.

337
00:18:57,067 --> 00:18:58,333
Emma...

338
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,300
Emma, you're not a killer.

339
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:02,500
This is not who you are.

340
00:19:03,633 --> 00:19:06,567
Danilo and Mookie don't know you
like this, so please...

341
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,300
please, put the gun down!

342
00:19:09,367 --> 00:19:11,067
What about you,
do we know you?

343
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:13,800
You're not the Jade
that we used to know!

344
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:15,967
You seemed possessed!

345
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:18,100
You've changed into a monster!

346
00:19:18,233 --> 00:19:20,767
Emma, please,
can we talk about this?

347
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,267
Put the gun down.

348
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:27,433
If you want, we can share them.

349
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,233
We can share them.

350
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,467
You can have them on Mondays,
Wednesdays, and Fridays.

351
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,600
I can have them on Tuesdays,
Thursdays, and Saturdays.

352
00:19:32,733 --> 00:19:34,100
It's all good!

353
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:36,400
Everybody's happy, right?

354
00:19:36,533 --> 00:19:39,133
What do you think they are?
A pizza?

355
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:43,933
I will never give you
what belongs to me.

356
00:19:44,067 --> 00:19:46,633
Emma, please, I am begging you.

357
00:19:46,767 --> 00:19:48,167
I am begging you.

358
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:51,733
Please, put that down,
don't do this.

359
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:55,433
Please, Emma, let's fix
and talk about this.

360
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:57,333
Let's start from the beginning.

361
00:19:58,433 --> 00:20:00,667
Do you really want me
to put the gun down?

362
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,267
And forget everything
that happened?

363
00:20:02,433 --> 00:20:03,700
Yes, Emma.

364
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:07,733
Let's start again as a one
big happy family.

365
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:10,333
A peaceful family,
a proper one.

366
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:14,533
-Please, Emma, put the gun down.
-Peaceful? A proper one?

367
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:16,133
Aren't you the one
who's causing all the trouble?

368
00:20:16,267 --> 00:20:18,433
I'm begging you, please.

369
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:21,600
Please. I will do anything
you want.

370
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:24,567
- Just put the gun down. Please!
- You really want me

371
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:25,933
to put the gun down?

372
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:27,033
Yes! Yes!

373
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:28,600
You want to forget
this happened?

374
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:30,567
I will do anything, Emma.

375
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,900
Anything you want.

376
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,000
Look...

377
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:37,967
look at yourself.
You look like a defeated dog.

378
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,967
Eat that dog food.

379
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:43,767
No!

380
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,100
No!

381
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:47,900
I won't eat that!
That's so gross!

382
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:50,533
Emma, I will do anything
but not that! Please!

383
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:51,733
Are you going to eat
that dog food

384
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:53,700
or do you want me
to feed you this bullet?

385
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:54,500
Fine!

386
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:55,767
Fine!

387
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:23,100
Emma, please.
Don't make me do this, please.

388
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:24,100
Eat it!

389
00:21:24,233 --> 00:21:25,567
Fine!

390
00:21:25,700 --> 00:21:27,167
I will!

391
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:47,267
There you go. What a good girl!

392
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:51,467
Now you know how it feels
to lose a family!

393
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,200
To lose your dignity!

394
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:58,700
To be treated like garbage,
like a helpless animal!

395
00:21:58,833 --> 00:22:02,467
That's just a fraction
of what you did to me, Jade!

396
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,867
<i>We will help you
if you need help.</i>

397
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,433
<i> You need professional help!</i>

398
00:22:06,567 --> 00:22:09,233
<i> Mookie! Danilo!</i>

399
00:22:09,667 --> 00:22:11,667
<i> Mookie!</i>

400
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,833
<i> I'm not crazy!</i>

401
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:16,167
Stop!

402
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:20,300
I don't deserve
this humiliation!

403
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:24,367
I don't ask for too much, Emma.

404
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:30,533
I just want to feel loved.

405
00:22:30,667 --> 00:22:33,200
To be loved
by Danilo and Mookie.

406
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,633
Is that too much to ask?

407
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,533
Don't I deserve some love?

408
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:38,133
Love?

409
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:40,967
Something you stole from me
and doesn't belong to you!

410
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,033
Why are you so stingy, Emma?

411
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:50,133
You grew up with Ligaya,
didn't you?

412
00:22:51,233 --> 00:22:53,367
You have Danilo...

413
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,133
and Mookie.

414
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:57,500
You have everything you wanted!

415
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:01,267
What makes you so special?

416
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:04,300
That you get to have everything
that you want in life?

417
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:06,633
What about me?

418
00:23:07,633 --> 00:23:09,667
What do I have?

419
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:10,767
I have nothing!

420
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:13,867
What about me?

421
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:17,267
Is it wrong to ask
for what you have?

422
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:19,000
Stealing is a sin!

423
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:22,633
In God's eyes and human law,
you know that it's wrong!

424
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,133
So have some decency!

425
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:26,100
Fine!

426
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:28,033
I'm wrong!

427
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,433
What I did is wrong!

428
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:31,833
I'm a monster!

429
00:23:31,967 --> 00:23:33,467
So go ahead!

430
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,300
Shoot me!

431
00:23:35,433 --> 00:23:38,033
Let's stop this
once and for all!

432
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:39,600
You win.

433
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,500
Danilo and Mookie
are all yours!

434
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:43,833
We're even now!

435
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,600
Because after all this...

436
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:50,067
you will become a killer, too.

437
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,167
You're so dramatic!

438
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:54,333
You're calling me a killer?

439
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,500
Isn't it possible

440
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:59,233
that I quickly removed
the magazine from the gun

441
00:23:59,367 --> 00:24:01,267
before I played with you?

442
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,333
You lying snake!

443
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:09,867
You're losing your mind,
aren't you?

444
00:24:10,967 --> 00:24:12,600
Just like Olive.

445
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,400
How dare you!

446
00:24:16,533 --> 00:24:18,900
- Mom!
- Emma!

447
00:24:19,033 --> 00:24:20,433
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

448
00:24:20,567 --> 00:24:23,300
- Mookie, she has a gun!
- Help me!

449
00:24:23,433 --> 00:24:24,633
Emma, put the gun down!

450
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:26,033
Mookie!

451
00:24:26,167 --> 00:24:30,300
Mookie, look at what your mom
is doing to me!

452
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:36,900
Hello, Caloy.

453
00:24:37,033 --> 00:24:38,767
An officer is waiting
outside the house.

454
00:24:38,900 --> 00:24:40,667
He's with the guy
who's acquainted with Ligaya.

455
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,667
<i>Looks like they're looking
for Ligaya.</i>

456
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:43,967
What?

457
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:46,333
Where is the path
that leads to her room?

458
00:24:46,467 --> 00:24:46,900
It's over this way.

459
00:24:47,033 --> 00:24:48,400
Dad...

460
00:24:48,533 --> 00:24:51,033
why is Mommy Emma
acting like that?

461
00:24:51,167 --> 00:24:54,833
I saw how much hatred
she had for Aunt Jade

462
00:24:54,967 --> 00:24:56,567
while pointing a gun at her.

463
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:59,100
Perhaps I was right
when I said before

464
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:01,933
that she's turning out
to be like Mommy Olive.

465
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:03,600
I will never give up.

466
00:25:03,733 --> 00:25:09,033
I will do everything I can
to escape this hell hole.

467
00:25:09,167 --> 00:25:10,900
Ligaya?
